sections.markdown:
# This is a sample notebook to analyze logs
Create your own Notebook or copy this one. Then  experiment with DQL (Dynatrace Query Language)

grail.canonicalQuery:
fetch logs, from:now() - 10m
| summarize by:{loglevel}, count(), alias:logCount
| sort logCount, direction:"descending"

sections.title: Logs over time split by loglevel

grail.canonicalQuery:
fetch logs
| sort timestamp, direction:"descending"
| summarize by:{{bin(timestamp, 1m), alias:`1m interval`}, loglevel}, count(), alias:count
